heading: Is better educational attainment a job guarantee?
subheading: The employment rate among the population with a tertiary education in 2023 is as high as 86.3%.
textNote: The employment rate is calculated for people aged 20-64 years who had attained a high level of education. Tertiary education refers to ISCED levels 5-8. For low level of education (ISCED levels 0-2), the rate stands at 58.3 %. For medium level of education the rate stands at 74.6 % (ISCED levels 3-4).
